# Hook Naming & Structure

## Naming Convention
- Prefix with 'use'
- Camel case after prefix
- Descriptive of functionality
- Examples: useVaultMemories, useAudioRecorder

## Structure
- Single responsibility principle
- Return consistent interface
- Handle loading/error/success states
- Support TypeScript generics where appropriate
- Document return type explicitly

## State Management
- Include isLoading boolean
- Include error handling
- Include success state
- Support optimistic updates
- Handle offline state if data-related

## Error Handling
- Try/catch for async operations
- Proper error typing
- Error message formatting
- Recovery mechanisms
- Retry logic where appropriate

## Performance
- Memoize expensive calculations
- Debounce rapid changes
- Cache results when possible
- Clean up subscriptions
- Handle side effects properly 